HiveMind × Ravensbourne
Professional Research Interview Transcript
Introduction
This interview was conducted for the HiveMind × Ravensbourne UX Product Discovery
Sprint. The objective is to understand real workplace onboarding experiences and identify
opportunities for Smart Onboarding. The participant provided consent for audio recording
and agreed that their responses would be anonymised using Participant ID P01.
Participant Details
Participant ID P01
Role Business Analyst
Industry Technology
Company Size 500+ employees
Duration 35–40 minutes
Interview Transcript
[00:00] Interviewer: Thank you for joining today. Before we begin, is it okay if I record this
interview?
[00:10] Participant P01: Yes, that's absolutely fine.
[00:20] Interviewer: Can you briefly describe your current role?
[00:35] Participant P01: I work as a Business Analyst. I gather business requirements,
work with stakeholders and support digital transformation projects.
[02:00] Interviewer: Tell me about the last time you joined a new company.
[02:20] Participant P01: The first week was exciting but confusing. There were many
systems, documents and meetings. Nobody explained what should be completed first.
[04:10] Interviewer: What were the top three things you needed?
[04:30] Participant P01: Understanding my responsibilities, system access and knowing
who to contact.
[06:00] Interviewer: What was the hardest part?
[06:20] Participant P01: Finding updated documents because information was scattered
across Teams, SharePoint and email.
[08:00] Interviewer: Did onboarding feel useful?
[08:15] Participant P01: Some sessions were useful but many felt like generic compliance
training instead of helping me perform my role.
[10:00] Interviewer: Where do you usually look for information?
[10:20] Participant P01: Teams first, then SharePoint, then colleagues.
[12:00] Interviewer: Have you ever struggled to find important information?
[12:15] Participant P01: Yes. I once spent almost an hour searching for a project template
because different versions existed.
[14:00] Interviewer: How do you keep track of important documents?
[14:15] Participant P01: Bookmarks, OneNote and browser folders, but they quickly
become outdated.
[16:00] Interviewer: If you had one home screen, what would you want?
[16:20] Participant P01: Today's tasks, onboarding progress, key contacts, latest
documents and learning modules.
[18:00] Interviewer: What should always be easy to access?
[18:20] Participant P01: Policies, HR contacts, manager details, IT support and project
documentation.
[20:00] Interviewer: How do you know information is correct?
[20:20] Participant P01: Usually by checking document dates or confirming with my
manager.
[22:00] Interviewer: What would have made your first day easier?
[22:20] Participant P01: A personalised checklist with clear priorities.
[24:00] Interviewer: Did you know what to do each day?
[24:20] Participant P01: Not always. I often waited for someone to assign work.
[26:00] Interviewer: What makes onboarding feel personal?
[26:20] Participant P01: Role-specific content, manager check-ins and progress
milestones.
[28:00] Interviewer: Have you used AI at work?
[28:20] Participant P01: Yes. AI helps summarise documents but I only trust it when
sources are cited.
[30:00] Interviewer: When should AI tell users to ask a human?
[30:20] Participant P01: For HR decisions, salary, legal issues and sensitive policies.
[32:00] Interviewer: Do you have privacy concerns?
[32:20] Participant P01: Yes, unless I know company data is secure and access controlled.
[34:00] Interviewer: To wrap up, what are the top two onboarding problems?
[34:20] Participant P01: Scattered information and unclear priorities.
[35:00] Interviewer: What do those problems cost?
[35:15] Participant P01: Lost productivity, frustration and unnecessary delays.
[36:00] Interviewer: If you could change one thing?
[36:15] Participant P01: Create one Smart Onboarding platform with personalised
guidance, progress tracking and trusted AI support.
[37:00] Interviewer: Thank you for your time.
[37:10] Participant P01: You're welcome.
